>[Thoughts]
>I know inflation is when there is a decrease in the purchasing power 
>of money so all prices increase. So does this mean that I multiply 
>the inflation rate by the salary for a time period, say 25 years 
>using a spreadsheet? I know that with a repayment mortgage, the 
>interest will slowly decrease throughout the loan period. But the 
>fact that the prices of everything increase, does the interest and 
>repayments increase as well? I'm just not sure if what I'm thinking 
